The paper discusses advanced citation-based methods for identifying potential breakthrough papers, which are likely to be of interest to researchers in the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of clustering and filtering algorithms, which are commonly used in the fields of social informatics (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper evaluates the methods using publication sets linked to different funding instruments, which suggests a possible connection to computer and information science education (cs.CR).
